cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper describes a new instance-based learning algorithm that can be used for both supervised and unsupervised learning. This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv. Given that the algorithm is focused on learning from data, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the algorithm can be used for image classification (cs.CV), and it is flexible with regards to what data manifolds it can learn (cs.DS). The algorithm also has the potential to be used in artificial intelligence applications (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
